<body>

<header>
    <h1>U.S. Immigration Policy Discussion</h1>
    <p>Exploring arguments for stricter immigration policies</p>
</header>

<nav>
    <a href="#economy">Economy</a>
    <a href="#services">Public Services</a>
    <a href="#security">Security</a>
    <a href="#counter">Counterarguments</a>
</nav>

<div class="container">

    <h2 id="economy">Economic Considerations</h2>
    <p>
        Some argue that high levels of immigration can affect job markets, especially in lower-wage sectors.
        Increased competition may impact wages and employment opportunities for certain groups.
    </p>

    <h2 id="services">Strain on Public Services</h2>
    <p>
        Population growth can increase demand for schools, healthcare, and housing.
        Managing growth is important to ensure infrastructure keeps pace.
    </p>

    <h2 id="security">Border Security and Legal Systems</h2>
    <p>
        Maintaining secure borders and a structured immigration system is seen by some as essential for fairness
        and national stability.
    </p>

    <h2 id="counter">Counterarguments</h2>
    <p>
        Immigration also contributes to economic growth, innovation, and cultural diversity.
        Many sectors rely on immigrant workers, and immigrants have long played a key role in U.S. development.
    </p>

</div>

